txt.en: 'I ain't putting this one right! If Lugbúrz wants the Tower so badly, the Big Bosses can sort it out themselves!'
'That's enough chatter!'
Instance: Necessary Sacrifices
'Lugbúrz says you're lucky if Her Ladyship chooses you!'
'Lugbúrz said a lot. Lot of good that did 'em!'
'Did you hear that?'
'I thought I heard something, Captain--'
'Ahhhhhh!'
'Raaaaagh!'
'Her Ladyship's led us into a trap!'
'If this is how She's going to be, no meat for Her!'
'You lot, we're leaving. Now!'
'Silent One! Let's go!'
'Damned flies....'
'You lot, listen up!'
'Don't think you've gotten off easy! We're going to wait a bit for Her Ladyship!'
''Walk about, pick the bones, throw a damned stone into one of Her tunnels -- I don't care.'
'We wait as long as I say so!'
'[placeholder]! Hold just a moment, and I will free you!'
'Do not struggle! I have almost got you loose!'
'There! Let us go, [placeholder]!'
'Right then.'
'Get a move on, maggots. You'll have it worse if you turn back now!'
'What's this now?'
'You thought me a stupid Uruk, didn't you? Ah, but you're no Orc!'
'I knew straight away, [placeholder]! Who do you think made that wretch into the Silent One?'
'Hah! Well, She's got you now...and there's no escaping Her!'
'Maybe She'll make it quick, but I sure hope She doesn't!'
